                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Crude, angular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>Possibly written by <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11077Zadengel">Za-Dǝngǝl</persName>.<date>Second half of the 19th
                           cent.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; name of the protagonist and other
                           saints; names of the donors; incipits of Text I and its subsections
                           (fols. 8ra, 15vb, 24rb, 28ra, 33va, 44vb, 49vb, 57vb, 68ra, 74rb);
                           incipit of Text II; notes in the upper margin of some fols.; elements of
                           the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 On the incipit
                           page of Text I (fols. 3r), a few lines are rubricated (alternating with
                           black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
